Yes. I can write wolli extensions in TypeScript.

I can create extensions that:
- register custom tools
- add slash commands
- intercept/modify tool calls
- block dangerous actions
- add UI prompts/widgets/status
- persist extension state
- inject context or modify prompts
- hot-reload via `/reload`

Typical location for this agent:

```bash
~/.wolli/agents/ricky2/extensions/my-extension.ts
```

Example extension shape:

```ts
import type { ExtensionAPI } from "@opsyhq/wolli";
import { Type } from "typebox";

export default function (wolli: ExtensionAPI) {
  wolli.registerCommand("hello", {
    description: "Say hello",
    handler: async (_args, ctx) => {
      ctx.ui.notify("Hello from extension", "info");
    },
  });

  wolli.registerTool({
    name: "greet",
    label: "Greet",
    description: "Greet someone",
    parameters: Type.Object({
      name: Type.String(),
    }),
    async execute(_id, params) {
      return {
        content: [{ type: "text", text: `Hello, ${params.name}` }],
      };
    },
  });
}
```

Tell me what extension you want and whether you want it installed for `ricky2` globally or project-local.
